Replit: Remix the Internet
// I=E2=80=99ve started and restarted this essay more times than any I=E2=
=80=99ve ever written. It=E2=80=99s a tough one. It=E2=80=99s hard to captu=
re the full breadth of what Replit is trying to build, and how, and what th=
e world will look like if they succeed. That=E2=80=99s partially because it=
=E2=80=99s impossible to predict, because Replit is in the primitives busin=
ess. It=E2=80=99s laying the foundation on top of which one billion people =
will build the future. After spending hours and hours researching, talking =
to Replit=E2=80=99s CEO Amjad Masad, and writing this piece, I=E2=80=99m co=
nvinced that Replit has the potential to be one of the most valuable and im=
pactful companies in the world. But I probably need to explain why, and to =
do that, I need to just pick a place to start and get going. So let=E2=80=
=99s start here.=C2=A0
Everyone=E2=80=99s first line of code has to be written in Replit.=C2=A0
Replit [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuxCAM_JrlGPFMyIFDL_sbEQEnQU=
sgAqdt_r7s5lDJsmWNxuMZZxHWXC5z5Irk3Sa8DjAJfmoERCjkrFCm4A3ruRZKjsQb6ZlWmoQ6L=
QVgtyEaLCeQ45xjcBZDTh8GpVyRzUglhV16pefBgeeCKe-VZIMYZs1Gx25de_oAyYGBbyhXTkCi=
2RCP-hBfD_5sVeCIATuX97aQYDjljHE6MqF6RjveLcBmSp2lWiwjk0snzo363xAfku4r7-o5V7T=
u9T5BikkZ51xCWhv82uwO8QM0F1Ob-5kCXhMkO0fwt0G8c_pYnlZIUFp-frLY0hEjVZrp9oy6Db=
UEpOK8p3wgTdnnxkr_on8eNX7D]=E2=80=99s mission is to bring the next billion =
software creators online and accelerate a shift towards a world where the c=
ombination of software and the internet is truly The Great Equalizer. The c=
ompany believes that in the modern world, the ability to write code should =
be as ubiquitous as the ability to write essays. It wants to lead the trans=
ition from a stacked model of software creation to a networked one, and to =
create the world=E2=80=99s first massively distributed and collaborative op=
