ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But when you&#8217;re setting out to =
build something as big as Replit wants to become, you need to start with a =
clear and ambitious <strong>proximate objective</strong>, something to tack=
le right now.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">That&#8217;s why Replit wants to be <strong=
>the first place that anyone writes a line of code</strong>. Then it can be=
come the first place they build an app, the first place they collaborate on=
 software, the first place they make money online, and ultimately, the plac=
e that they turn whenever they want to create software.&nbsp;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"=
>It&#8217;s a straightforward goal with nuanced implications.&nbsp;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em=
 0;">For example, it means <em>not </em>targeting experienced developers to=
 start, even though they&#8217;re the more valuable users today. If they&#8=
217;ve already written their first line of code elsewhere, they definitiona=
lly can&#8217;t write their first line of code in Replit.&nbsp;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"=
>It also means that Replit needs to make it really easy to get started by p=
utting everything you need to code something simple in one place, accessibl=
e from anywhere in the world with an internet connection whether you&#8217;=
re on a brand new MacBook Pro, a Chromebook, or even an Android phone.&nbsp=
;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 1em 0;">And it means making it multiplayer from the beginning, to cre=
ate a modern development experience that includes collaboration, like peopl=
e are used to with products like Google Docs and Figma. A networked operati=
ng system demands networked development.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1=
a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The approach com=
es with trade-offs. As it stands today, a large company couldn&#8217;t buil=
d most of its software in Replit. It&#8217;s more limited than a local setu=
p including best-in-class point-solutions like Microsoft&#8217;s VS Code, G=
ithub, Heroku, Docker, AWS, npm, and postgres. It&#8217;s slower. It&#8217;=
s not industrial-grade. But that&#8217;s not the point.&nbsp;</p><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"=
>Replit wants to build the future, and <strong>to build the future, you don=
&#8217;t rebuild the old thing for the old customers</strong>. You build so=
mething new that starts out <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx=
FkU2OhCAQhU_T7DD8qKMLFrOZaxiQUokIBsvp9vZT3S4mgVeByqtHPkaLMOdymT0fyN4y4LWDSf=
